The paper discusses the development of a haptic teleoperation setup for performing complex tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The focus is on improving the transparency of interaction, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and control systems (cs.SY). The use of a state-dependent impedance controller also involves mathematical optimization (cs.MA) and machine learning (cs.LG).
